id: pm-96h7
title: "Project relationship graph maturity: typed edge ontology, graph governance, scalable analytics, and all-status knowledge-map backfill"
description: "Make item relationships first-class, semantically typed, queryable, explainable, and useful from tiny projects to million-item multi-agent ecosystems without manufacturing meaningless edges."
type: Epic
status: open
priority: 1
tags[7]: "area:graph","area:sdk",context-management,governance,initiative,relationships,scale
created_at: "2026-07-13T21:57:05.806Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-17T10:11:06.228Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 1800
acceptance_criteria: "A reviewed ADR defines canonical and custom edge semantics, direction, ordering, inverse, provenance, and compatibility; The public SDK exposes bounded graph mutation and query primitives before thin CLI, MCP, and package adapters; Graph governance reports semantic errors, isolates, stale or redundant edges, cycles only over order-bearing kinds, and profile-aware coverage; Analytics provide explainable critical paths, blast radius, bottlenecks, communities, redundancy, and relevance signals with deterministic evidence; A resumable all-status backfill classifies every item as connected, intentional root or archive, waived, or remediation debt without synthetic related filler; Benchmarks demonstrate bounded memory, latency, and token output at one million items while preserving small-project ergonomics"
goal: project management = context management
objective: Turn the complete tracker into a trustworthy typed knowledge graph that agents and algorithms can traverse under bounded time and token budgets
value: "Every agent can recover why work exists, what it affects, what orders it, and which evidence supports it without dumping the tracker"
impact: "Enables graph algorithms, context optimization, critical-path planning, dependency integrity, and durable ecosystem understanding at every scale"
outcome: "A schema-extensible relationship model, SDK graph primitives, scalable analytics, governance audits, and evidence-backed all-status enrichment"
why_now: The live hierarchy is connected but the active dependency graph has 100 isolates and only a two-edge prerequisite depth; some documented prerequisites are not encoded
parent: pm-33cw
risk: high
confidence: high
